<catsoop-section>Instructions</catsoop-section>

<center>
<img src="COURSE/algorithms/panchang_paheli/panchang_paheli_2.png" alt="Panchang Paheli Instructions" height="400"/>
</center>

1. Take any 6 (out of the given 7) puzzle pieces and try to cover the entire calendar grid, except for today's date. If you aren't able to do it, try with a different set of 6 pieces.

2. Every puzzle piece is made up of five connected squares, each in a different arrangement. Such an arrangement of five squares connected edge to edge is called a **pentomino**.

3. The six pentomino pieces would cover 6 × 5 = 30 square grids, leaving only the desired date visible.

