<catsoop-section>What's Happening</catsoop-section>

**Polyominoes** are fascinating geometric shapes made by connecting squares edge-to-edge. They come in different sizes, starting from the simplest—dominoes—to more complex shapes like hexominoes. Let's explore these shapes and discover the beauty of mathematics through them!

**1. Dominoes (2 Squares)**

A domino is the simplest polyomino, made up of just two squares connected along one side. There's only **1 unique domino**.

**2. Trominoes (3 Squares)**

Trominoes are formed by connecting three squares. They come in **2 different shapes** (I-shape and L-shape).

**3. Tetrominoes (4 Squares)**

Tetrominoes are made by joining four squares. These shapes are famous from the game **Tetris**! There are **5 unique tetrominoes**.

**4. Pentominoes (5 Squares)**

Pentominoes are created by linking five squares. There are **12 different pentomino shapes**.

**5. Hexominoes (6 Squares)**

Hexominoes are made by connecting six squares. These shapes start to get more complex, with **35 unique configurations**.

